lecDefaultLecsConfigType.name: lecDefaultLecsConfigType
lecDefaultLecsConfigType.description: Default configuration type of the LECS, see lecConfLecsConfigType (which overrides this variable) for more information on config type

lecDefaultLecsAtmAddress.name: lecDefaultLecsAtmAddress
lecDefaultLecsAtmAddress.description: Default LECS Atm Address to use for each LEC, can be overridden by lecConfLecsAtmAddress

lecConfTable.name: lecConfTable
lecConfTable.description: A table of LECs and their parameters.

lecConfEntry.name: lecConfEntry
lecConfEntry.description: A table entry contaning LEC parameters.

lecConfAtmAddress.name: lecConfAtmAddress
lecConfAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of this LEC

lecConfAdminStatus.name: lecConfAdminStatus
lecConfAdminStatus.description: The desired state for this LEC, the default value for this variable is up(1)

lecConfOperStatus.name: lecConfOperStatus
lecConfOperStatus.description: The actual status of this LEC

lecConfElanName.name: lecConfElanName
lecConfElanName.description: Name of the emulated lan to join

lecConfMacAddress.name: lecConfMacAddress
lecConfMacAddress.description: MAC address assigned to this LEC

lecConfLecsConfigType.name: lecConfLecsConfigType
lecConfLecsConfigType.description: One of: wellknown(1), manual(2). The default configuration type of the LEC is based on the default value set in the lecDefaultConfigType variable. wellknown(1) means that the LEC will try to find LECS in the manner specified in the spec (ILMI, WellKnown, PVC). manual(2) means that the LEC will use the address specified in the lecConfLecsAtmAddress variable.

lecConfLecsAtmAddress.name: lecConfLecsAtmAddress
lecConfLecsAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of LECS. The default ATM address of the LECS server is based on the default value set in the lecDefaultLecsAtmAddress variable. When the lecConfLecsConfigType is set to manual(2), this variable will be set to the Wellknown LECS address.

lecConfLesAtmAddress.name: lecConfLesAtmAddress
lecConfLesAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of LES to join. If The lecConfLecsConfigType is set to manual(2) and this variable is set to address of an LES, this address will be used as the address of the LES to join.

lecConfEntryStatus.name: lecConfEntryStatus
lecConfEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry, one of: valid(1), createRequest(2), underCreation(3), invalid(4)

lecConfIfName.name: lecConfIfName
lecConfIfName.description: Name of the interface associated with this LEC.

elarpFlush.name: elarpFlush
elarpFlush.description: This variable causes the LEC ARP cache to be flushed when it is set to enable(1).

lecArpTable.name: lecArpTable
lecArpTable.description: A table of LEC ARP entries.

lecArpEntry.name: lecArpEntry
lecArpEntry.description: A table entry contaning LEC ARP parameters.

lecArpMacAddress.name: lecArpMacAddress
lecArpMacAddress.description: MAC address of this ARP entry.

lecArpAtmAddress.name: lecArpAtmAddress
lecArpAtmAddress.description: The ATM address associated with this ARP entry.

lecArpFlags.name: lecArpFlags
lecArpFlags.description: The flags associated with this ARP entry.

lecArpConnVPI.name: lecArpConnVPI
lecArpConnVPI.description: The VPI associated with this connection.

lecArpConnVCI.name: lecArpConnVCI
lecArpConnVCI.description: The VCI associated with this connection.

lecArpFlush.name: lecArpFlush
lecArpFlush.description: When set to enable(1), will flush this entry from ARP cache.

lecArpElanName.name: lecArpElanName
lecArpElanName.description: Name of the emulated lan associated with this arp entry.

lesConfTable.name: lesConfTable
lesConfTable.description: A table of LESes and their parameters.

lesConfEntry.name: lesConfEntry
lesConfEntry.description: A table entry contaning LES parameters.

lesConfAtmAddress.name: lesConfAtmAddress
lesConfAtmAddress.description: The Atm address of this LES

lesConfAdminStatus.name: lesConfAdminStatus
lesConfAdminStatus.description: The desired state for this LES

lesConfOperStatus.name: lesConfOperStatus
lesConfOperStatus.description: The actual status of this LES

lesConfBusAtmAddress.name: lesConfBusAtmAddress
lesConfBusAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the BUS associated with this LES

lesConfBusMaster.name: lesConfBusMaster
lesConfBusMaster.description: The configuration of the BUS associated with this LES. When this variable is set to enable(1), the LES will attempt to start the BUS on the current host.

lesConfEntryStatus.name: lesConfEntryStatus
lesConfEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry, one of: valid(1), createRequest(2), underCreation(3), invalid(4)

lesConfLanType.name: lesConfLanType
lesConfLanType.description: The LAN type of this LES, one of: unspecified(1), aflane8023(2), aflane8025(3). When unspecified, the LES may attempt to discover the LAN type from the LECS, or simply choose a default value.

lesConfMaxFrameSize.name: lesConfMaxFrameSize
lesConfMaxFrameSize.description: The Maximum Frame Size of this LES, one of: unspecified(1), max1516(2), max4544(3), max9234(4), max18190(5), max1580(6). When unspecified, the LES may attempt to discover the Maximum Frame Size from the LECS, or simply choose a value commensurate with the LAN type.

lesConfSecureServer.name: lesConfSecureServer
lesConfSecureServer.description: The configuration of a secure LES or insecure LES.

lesConfLECSAtmAddress.name: lesConfLECSAtmAddress
lesConfLECSAtmAddress.description: The LECS atm address used when running with lesConfSecureServer enabled.

lesConfAnycastAtmAddress.name: lesConfAnycastAtmAddress
lesConfAnycastAtmAddress.description: The Anycast atm address used by clients to connect to one of the Les Servers

lesConfRegisterTLVs.name: lesConfRegisterTLVs
lesConfRegisterTLVs.description: The configuration of a server to forward (or not) registration TLVs.

lesConfElanId.name: lesConfElanId
lesConfElanId.description: The configuration of a numeric (non-zero) ELAN identifier.

lesConfTokenRingNumber.name: lesConfTokenRingNumber
lesConfTokenRingNumber.description: 12-bit hexadecimal ring (segment) number for a token ring ELAN.

lesConfForwardArp.name: lesConfForwardArp
lesConfForwardArp.description: The configuration of the LES to flood all LE-ARP requests to all clients, both proxy and non-proxy.

lesLnniConfTable.name: lesLnniConfTable
lesLnniConfTable.description: A table of entries to LNNI information about LESs.

lesLnniConfEntry.name: lesLnniConfEntry
lesLnniConfEntry.description: A table entry contaning LNNI parameters to LESes. LESes are identified by their lesConfIndex parameter.

lesLnniConfAtmAddress.name: lesLnniConfAtmAddress
lesLnniConfAtmAddress.description: The Atm address of a partner LES.

lesLnniConfEntryStatus.name: lesLnniConfEntryStatus
lesLnniConfEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry, one of: valid(1), createRequest(2), underCreation(3), invalid(4)

lesLeqConfLesId.name: lesLeqConfLesId
lesLeqConfLesId.description: The value of the lesConfIndex for the LES on which the leq command will be run when the lesLeqTableReload variable is set to go.

lesLeqTableReload.name: lesLeqTableReload
lesLeqTableReload.description: The current status of lesLeqTable update for the LES whose index is specified in lesLeqConfLesId. Is idle when the before it is set. To update the lesLeqTable content corresponding to this LES set this to go. A manager may restart the table update process by setting this entry to go when it is in the succeeded or failed states. This variable may be read-only in in inProgress state or may allow sets to idle.

lesLeqStatLesId.name: lesLeqStatLesId
lesLeqStatLesId.description: The value of the lesConfIndex for the LES on which the leq command was most recently run and the lesLeqTable was populated for.

lesLeqLastTime.name: lesLeqLastTime
lesLeqLastTime.description: The value of sysUptime the time the last request to fill in the lesLeqTable was finished.

lesLeqTable.name: lesLeqTable
lesLeqTable.description: This table contains all LAN Emulation clients serviced by a LES specified in lesLeqLesId. This table is generated from the output of the leq command. Details of the leq command can be found else where.

lesLeqEntry.name: lesLeqEntry
lesLeqEntry.description: Each entry represents a LANE client.

lesLeqIndex.name: lesLeqIndex
lesLeqIndex.description: An integer which is the index of the LANE client and uniquely identifies a LEC in this table.

lesLeqNsap.name: lesLeqNsap
lesLeqNsap.description: The NSAP address of the LANE client. This is the primary NSAP address of the LEC used in joining phase

lesLeqName.name: lesLeqName
lesLeqName.description: This is the comment field sent by the LEC to the LES during joining phase. This comment will contain the hostname of the machine where the LEC was started

busConfTable.name: busConfTable
busConfTable.description: A table of BUSes and their parameters.

busConfEntry.name: busConfEntry
busConfEntry.description: A table entry contaning BUS parameters.

busConfAtmAddress.name: busConfAtmAddress
busConfAtmAddress.description: The Atm address of this BUS

busConfAdminStatus.description: The desired state for this BUS

busConfOperStatus.name: busConfOperStatus
busConfOperStatus.description: The actual status of this BUS

busConfEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry, one of: valid(1), createRequest(2), underCreation(3), invalid(4)

busConfLanType.name: busConfLanType
busConfLanType.description: The LAN type of this BUS, one of: unspecified(1), aflane8023(2), aflane8025(3). When unspecified, the BUS may attempt to discover the LAN type from signaling IEs, or simply choose a default value.

busConfMaxFrameSize.name: busConfMaxFrameSize
busConfMaxFrameSize.description: The Maximum Frame Size of this BUS, one of: unspecified(1), max1516(2), max4544(3), max9234(4), max18190(5), max1580(6). When unspecified, the BUS may attempt to discover the Maximum Frame Size from signaling IEs, or simply handle the maximum.

lecsConfTable.name: lecsConfTable
lecsConfTable.description: A table of LECSes and their parameters.

lecsConfEntry.description: A table entry contaning LECS parameters.

lecsConfAtmAddress.name: lecsConfAtmAddress
lecsConfAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of this LECS

lecsConfDatabase.name: lecsConfDatabase
lecsConfDatabase.description: The full path to the location and name of the LECS database.

lecsConfEntryStatus.name: lecsConfEntryStatus
lecsConfEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry, one of: valid(1), createRequest(2), underCreation(3), invalid(4)

lecsConfDefaultLesFlag.name: lecsConfDefaultLesFlag
lecsConfDefaultLesFlag.description: The option to use the default LES ATM-address if the configuration file is inaccessible, one of: enable(1), disable(2)

lecsConfDefaultLesAtmAddress.name: lecsConfDefaultLesAtmAddress
lecsConfDefaultLesAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the default LES

lecsConfWellKnownAddressFlag.name: lecsConfWellKnownAddressFlag
lecsConfWellKnownAddressFlag.description: The option to disable the LECS well-known address, one of: none(1), atm-forum(2), other(3)

lecsConfWellKnownAddress.name: lecsConfWellKnownAddress
lecsConfWellKnownAddress.description: The well-known address for the LECS
